        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I was thinking about this too, but `get_client_by_id` is just too simple and useful. Yes, `get_clients` can do the same thing, but for the cases where I just want a client from an id (which is common), I find it clumsy with too much additional friction.\n\nIf you desperately want to avoid an alias, then I think it would be better to remove `id` as a filter, and potentially rename it to `get_client` to allow for potential future overloads in the future.",
