        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I wouldn't call that an improvement over what we have now as it still returns a table that needs to be indexed.\n\nThe only way I think we can remove this in a way that benefits the system, would be to also remove the applications for it's use.\n\nWe currently use it in our code as opposed to upval'ing the client object to check if a client is still valid. If we could add better state tracking to the clients, then we can change our APIs to pass objects around instead of IDs. This would eliminate most uses of `get_client_by_id`. There would be a bunch of breaking changes along the way, so needs a thought out plan.",
