        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I agree with Lewis, having a method that returns a single client instead of the table is useful - and that's despite Lua's `nil[1] -> nil` behavior making the list lookup less painful than it would be in other languages. The information in the type that there is at most one result is useful.\r\n\r\nBesides - the method's implementation is a single line, [it's used a lot](https://github.com/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=get_client_by_id+language%3Alua&type=code) and would cause a lot of churn. I'd rather use up the budget for user's tolerance for breaking changes of more impactful stuff.",
