        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "\r\n> Besides - the method's implementation is a single line, [it's used a lot](https://github.com/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=get_client_by_id+language%3Alua&type=code) and would cause a lot of churn. I'd rather use up the budget for user's tolerance for breaking changes of more impactful stuff.\r\n\r\nImplementation cost is often not the main cost. Rather, the presence of a single case is used to justify proliferation and sets the expectation of similar pattern in other modules. Its mere presence is confusing and counterproductive.\r\n\r\nThat is the primary purpose of most deprecations. Because the implementation cost is usually a sunk cost. Thus keeping the programmatic functionality around for back-compat is often worthwhile and cheap. But deprecating it--removing it from docs and human-visible surface area--gives a valuable signal about recommended patterns, reduces code review time, etc.\r\n\r\nIf we take that approach, then users won't be bothered by plugin breakage. Is there still an objection?",
            "created_at": "2024-10-26T14:26:34Z",
